			"text": "Trachymetopon is the largest coelacanthiform alongside the famous Mawsonia. It has been known from finds across Europe, but a basisphenoid found in Switzerland belonged to an individual that is estimated to have been about 5 meters long! The animal is also known from a full specimen in Germany and some fragments in France. Swimming in the Jurassic European oceans, Trachymetopon is among the few exclusively marine mawsoniids."
